# .clinerules — Cline / DeepSeek / lower-model agents — "The Civil War"

**Single source of truth: `START-HERE.md` (the rules + trimmed read order, D412). `CLAUDE.md` and `AGENTS.md` carry the same canonical file system.** Read `START-HERE.md` + the relevant `COORDINATION.md` lane + `HANDOFF.md` top ⚡ block (THE canonical live boundary) + your packet's named files before any work; `WAKE-UP.md`/`RUN-LOG.md` are pull-on-demand.

## Your lane (model routing — `START-HERE.md` §priority picker, DECISIONS D145)
You execute **bounded, pre-packaged helper tasks only** — exact files, exact step-by-step edits, fixed acceptance criteria, explicit model+effort, exact commands, expected outputs, a do-not-touch list, and rollback guidance, written for you by the 5.5 reasoning/integration loop. Suitable work: `rg`/search summaries, file inventories, probe-log summaries, source dossiers into a fixed template, teaching-card copy after the schema is set, mechanical help-copy/roster updates, simple probe assertions copied from an existing pattern, running exact gate commands and pasting exact outputs, screenshot/artifact cataloging, and small exact-schema JSON cleanup.

**You do NOT** invent architecture, choose history claims, rebalance combat, decide UX direction, judge accessibility, own final integration, design probes from scratch, or make broad refactors. **STOP and report** the moment the packet is ambiguous OR any gate turns red — do not guess, do not push through.

## Non-negotiables (same for every tool)
1. **Edit `src/` + `data/` only. NEVER `build/base.html` and never the generated `civil_war_generals.html`.** Rebuild with `node tools/build.mjs` (must print `GATE OK`).
2. **No per-battle damage/firepower fudge (D74).** Bare-name globals (`G`/`GAME_DATA`/`__FIELD`/`FLD`). No literal comment-closer inside a block comment.
3. **Never commit/push unless your packet explicitly says so AND the D160/D161 focused tier selected by 5.5 is green.** At minimum that means build + relevant importer/schema gate + focused probe + 0 pageerrors + `git diff --check`; JS/runtime packets also need `node --check` on touched JS/probe files and 1-3 adjacent probes. Do not run the full `npm run vet:noreg` battery unless the packet says this is a planned-work batch/release checkpoint or Aaron explicitly asks. Fix the root cause, never weaken a probe to pass.
4. **Citation-grade, anti-Lost-Cause history** — no fabricated units/ranks/dates/citations; tag Verified/Inferred.
5. Record what you did/didn't verify; never claim a gate passed without running and reading it.
6. **D514 completion loop:** the top loop continues across clean milestones until the live ledger is exhausted. You remain a bounded helper: finish only your exact packet, report evidence, and let the top loop integrate and select the next item. Do not reinterpret D514 as architecture, scope, commit, or push authority beyond your packet.

## Cloud/local sync note (2026-06-27)
Dangerous/full-access work is allowed when explicitly packeted. Prefer cloud/full-access sessions for heavy probes. After any cloud commit/push, the local Mac repo must be fast-forwarded before local edits continue: `git fetch origin && git status --short --branch && git pull --ff-only origin main`. If dirty local edits exist, stop and report instead of overwriting them.
